# Infrastructure as Code (Bicep) Rules & Best Practices

## Mandatory Bicep Rules (MUST FOLLOW)

### 1. Resource Naming Convention
- **Format**: `az{resourcePrefix}{resourceToken}`
- **resourcePrefix**: 2-3 alphanumeric characters (max 3), lowercase
- **resourceToken**: `uniqueString(subscription().id, resourceGroup().id, location, environmentName)`
- **Example**: `acrMcb{uniqueString}`, `caeMcb{uniqueString}`

### 2. Resource Location Handling
- **IMPORTANT**: Check available regions/SKUs for each resource type BEFORE writing Bicep
- **Must call**: `appmod-get-available-region-sku` to validate regions
- **Rule**: Resources should be in available regions; if not, choose alternate region and add index suffix
- **Scope**: Each resource can have different location (not limited to resource group location)

### 3. File Structure
```
infra/
├── main.bicep                     # Main template
├── main.parameters.json           # Parameter values
└── variables.bicep (optional)     # Variable definitions
```

### 4. Parameter File (`main.parameters.json`)
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentParameters.json#",
  "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "parameters": {
    "environmentName": {
      "value": "prod"
    },
    "location": {
      "value": "eastus"
    }
  }
}
```

### 5. Deployment Scope
- **Scope**: resourceGroup (for Container Apps deployment)
- **API Version**: Use latest stable versions
  - Container Apps: `2024-03-01`
  - Container Registry: `2023-07-01`
  - Managed Identity: `2023-01-31`
  - Log Analytics: `2021-12-01-preview`

---

## Container Apps Specific Rules (MANDATORY)

### 1. Managed Identity Configuration
```bicep
// MUST use User-Assigned Identity (NOT system-assigned)
var userIdentityName = 'id-${resourceToken}'

resource userIdentity 'Microsoft.ManagedIdentity/userAssignedIdentities@2023-01-31' = {
  name: userIdentityName
  location: location
  // ...
}

resource containerApp 'Microsoft.App/containerApps@2024-03-01' = {
  identity: {
    type: 'UserAssigned'
    userAssignedIdentities: {
      '${userIdentity.id}': {}
    }
  }
  // ...
}
```

### 2. AcrPull Role Assignment (MANDATORY, BEFORE container app)
```bicep
resource acrPullRoleAssignment 'Microsoft.Authorization/roleAssignments@2022-04-01' = {
  scope: containerRegistry
  name: guid(containerRegistry.id, userIdentity.id, 'acrpull')
  properties: {
    roleDefinitionId: subscriptionResourceId('Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions', '7f951dda-4ed3-4680-a7ca-43fe172d538d') // AcrPull
    principalId: userIdentity.properties.principalId
    principalType: 'ServicePrincipal'
  }
  dependsOn: [
    userIdentity
  ]
}
```

### 3. Container Registry Connection
```bicep
resource containerApp 'Microsoft.App/containerApps@2024-03-01' = {
  properties: {
    configuration: {
      registries: [
        {
          server: containerRegistry.properties.loginServer
          username: containerRegistry.name // or use admin user
          passwordSecretRef: 'registry-password'  // if using admin creds
          identity: userIdentity.id  // MUST use managed identity
        }
      ]
      secrets: [] // Define if needed
      ingress: {
        external: true
        targetPort: 5000
        corsPolicy: {
          allowedOrigins: ['*']
          allowedMethods: ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'DELETE', 'OPTIONS']
          allowedHeaders: ['*']
          exposeHeaders: ['*']
          maxAge: 3600
        }
      }
    }
    template: {
      containers: [
        {
          name: 'main-app'
          image: 'mcr.microsoft.com/azuredocs/containerapps-helloworld:latest' // Starting image
          resources: {
            cpu: json('0.25')
            memory: '0.5Gi'
          }
          env: [
            {
              name: 'FLASK_ENV'
              value: 'production'
            }
            {
              name: 'FLASK_APP'
              value: 'main.py'
            }
            {
              name: 'PORT'
              value: '5000'
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
      scale: {
        minReplicas: 1
        maxReplicas: 3
        rules: [
          {
            name: 'cpu-rule'
            custom: {
              query: 'cpu'
              metadata: {
                type: 'Utilization'
                value: '80'
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
  dependsOn: [
    acrPullRoleAssignment  // MUST wait for role assignment
    logAnalyticsWorkspace
  ]
  // ...
}
```

### 4. Log Analytics Connection (MANDATORY)
```bicep
resource containerAppEnvironment 'Microsoft.App/managedEnvironments@2024-03-01' = {
  properties: {
    logAnalyticsConfiguration: {
      customerId: logAnalyticsWorkspace.properties.customerId
      sharedKey: logAnalyticsWorkspace.listKeys().primarySharedKey
    }
  }
}
```

### 5. Base Image Requirement
- **MUST** start with: `mcr.microsoft.com/azuredocs/containerapps-helloworld:latest`
- Later replaced by deployment pipeline with actual app image

---

## Container Registry Rules

### 1. Admin User Configuration
```bicep
resource containerRegistry 'Microsoft.ContainerRegistry/registries@2023-07-01' = {
  properties: {
    adminUserEnabled: true  // Enable for managed identity access
    publicNetworkAccess: 'Enabled'
    networkRuleBypassOptions: 'AzureServices'
  }
}
```

### 2. Image Pull Secret (if using admin credentials)
```bicep
resource containerApp 'Microsoft.App/containerApps@2024-03-01' = {
  properties: {
    configuration: {
      secrets: [
        {
          name: 'registry-password'
          value: containerRegistry.listCredentials().passwords[0].value
        }
      ]
      registries: [
        {
          server: containerRegistry.properties.loginServer
          username: containerRegistry.listCredentials().username
          passwordSecretRef: 'registry-password'
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Log Analytics & Application Insights Rules

### 1. Log Analytics Workspace
```bicep
resource logAnalyticsWorkspace 'Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces@2021-12-01-preview' = {
  name: 'law-${resourceToken}'
  location: location
  properties: {
    sku: {
      name: 'PerGB2018'
    }
    retentionInDays: 30
  }
}
```

### 2. Application Insights
```bicep
resource appInsights 'Microsoft.Insights/components@2020-02-02' = {
  name: 'ai-${resourceToken}'
  location: location
  kind: 'web'
  properties: {
    Application_Type: 'web'
    WorkspaceResourceId: logAnalyticsWorkspace.id
    RetentionInDays: 30
  }
}
```

---

## Validation Checklist

Before deployment, validate:
- [ ] All resource names follow `az{prefix}{token}` format
- [ ] `resourceToken` computed correctly: `uniqueString(subscription().id, resourceGroup().id, location, environmentName)`
- [ ] User-Assigned Managed Identity attached to Container App (not system)
- [ ] AcrPull role assignment created BEFORE container app
- [ ] Container App depends on Log Analytics Workspace
- [ ] Registry connection uses managed identity
- [ ] CORS enabled on Container App ingress
- [ ] Base image is MCR hello-world (to be replaced by pipeline)
- [ ] Port 5000 exposed via ingress
- [ ] Environment variables configured (FLASK_ENV, FLASK_APP, PORT)

## Bicep Syntax Validation

```powershell
# Validate Bicep syntax before deployment
az bicep build --file infra/main.bicep

# Validate deployment would succeed (dry-run)
az deployment group validate \
  --resource-group mcb-prod \
  --template-file infra/main.bicep \
  --parameters infra/main.parameters.json
```

---

## Deployment Commands

```powershell
# Deploy to resource group
az deployment group create `
  --name mcb-deploy-$(Get-Date -Format "yyyyMMddHHmmss") `
  --resource-group mcb-prod `
  --template-file infra/main.bicep `
  --parameters infra/main.parameters.json

# Preview changes (plan mode)
az deployment group create `
  --resource-group mcb-prod `
  --template-file infra/main.bicep `
  --parameters infra/main.parameters.json `
  --what-if
```

---

## Common Errors & Fixes

| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| "Field 'configuration.secrets' is invalid" | Managed identity cannot access Key Vault | Use direct connection string in env var first, then migrate to Key Vault |
| "Insufficient permissions" | Managed identity missing role assignment | Ensure AcrPull role is assigned to managed identity on ACR |
| "Registry not found" | Registry connection misconfigured | Verify registry server FQDN and authentication method |
| "Image pull failed" | Base image path incorrect | Use full MCR URL: `mcr.microsoft.com/azuredocs/containerapps-helloworld:latest` |

